        <div id="documentationContent"><div class="documentationSection"><div class="documentationSectionContent">
<p><strong>MailChecker</strong> is a QA tool for automated checking of emails and their localizations.
This document describes the architecture of theMailchecker system, detailing its components,
their interactions, and deployment environments. It is intended primarily for the MailChecker
development team.</p>
</div></div><div class="documentationSection"><div class="documentationSectionContent"><a name="1"></a><a name="context" class="headingAnchor"></a><h2>1 Context</h2>
<p>Mailchecker uses several extrenal systems for notification via MS Teams,
fetches emails from Gmail and send mtrics to the Prometheus.</p>
<p>It's built on Flask for backend processes, Vue2 for the frontend, Selenium
grid for browser page rendering, Redis for data storage, and Google Cloud Storage
for screenshot archiving. This streamlined tool enhances team collaboration
and data management.</p>
