<a name="2.2"></a><a name="backend" class="headingAnchor"></a><h3>2.2 Backend</h3>
<p>The backend diagram goes deeper into the internal workings of the Mailchecker's backend.
It illustrates the network of components such as the Celery tasks, Parser, and various
APIs that collaborate to process, analyze, and manage emails efficiently.</p>
<p>It is a heart of Mailchecker, built on the Flask, which is complemented by a task
management system powered by Celery workers. This backend handling everything from email
parsing to report generation and synchronization with Gmail.</p>
<a name="2.2.1"></a><a name="main-mailcheckers-backend-features:" class="headingAnchor"></a><h4>2.2.1 Main Mailchecker's backend features:</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Email Parsing:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Prices (in email and in cart), Subject, Pre-Header and Title of email in browser</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Shopping Carts Parsing:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Prices, Product Name, Coupon, Campaign marker</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Links Parsing:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Locale, Title, Status Code, UTM</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Landing Pages Parsing</strong></li>
<li><strong>Validation of parsed data</strong></li>
<li><strong>Creating report</strong></li>
<li><strong>Automatic synchronization with Gmail</strong></li>
<li><strong>Automatic archiving of old emails</strong></li>
<li><strong>Storing emails for future preview</strong></li>
<li><strong>Storing Screenshots of emails</strong></li>
